Removing the constant condition can prevent an infinite loop from occurring if the condition never changes:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;
using UnityEngine;

public enum BoneId
{
	// The condition is always evaluating to false, not just never reaching the condition.
    // Therefore we don't change the condition, but remove the whole line:
    // Max = ((int)Hand_End > 50) ? (int)Hand_End : 50,
```

If the condition is only true or false once per condition, then removing the condition can also solve the problem:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;
using UnityEngine;

